How SAGA DP handles failure of any individual SAGA?
Рђб The saga pattern provides transaction management with using a sequence of local transactions of microservices. Every microservices has its own database and it can able to manage local transaction in atomic way with strict consistency.
Рђб So saga pattern grouping these local transactions and sequentially invoking one by one. Each local transaction updates the database and publishes an event to trigger the next local transaction.
Рђб If one of the step is failed, than saga patterns trigger to rollback transactions that are a set of compensating transactions that rollback the changes on previous microservices and restore data consistency.


Ways to Implement SAGA?
Рђб There are two type of saga implementation ways
Рђб choreography
Рђб orchestration


What is Choreography Saga Pattern?
Рђб Choreography is a way to coordinate sagas where participants exchange events without a centralized point of control
Рђб With choreography, each microservices run its own local transaction and publishes events to message broker system and that trigger local transactions in other microservices.

