1) JVM Architecture
­ЪЉЅ The Java Virtual Machine (JVM) executes Java bytecode. It sits between compiled .class files and the OS.
High-level Flow

Java Source (.java)  Рєњ  Compiler (javac)  Рєњ  Bytecode (.class)  Рєњ  JVM  Рєњ  Machine Code



Main Components
1. Class Loader Subsystem
    * Loads .class files into memory.
    * Phases: Loading Рєњ Linking Рєњ Initialization.
    * Delegation model (Bootstrap Рєњ Extension Рєњ Application classloader).
2. Runtime Data Areas
    * Method Area: Stores class metadata, static variables.
    * Heap: Stores objects (shared memory).
    * Stack: Each thread has its own stack Рєњ stores method frames, local variables.
    * PC Register: Stores address of current instruction for each thread.
    * Native Method Stack: For methods written in C/C++ (JNI).
3. Execution Engine
    * Interpreter: Reads bytecode line by line (slow).
    * JIT Compiler: Compiles hot code into native code for speed.
    * Garbage Collector (GC): Manages memory (removes unused objects).
4. Native Libraries
    * JNI interface Рєњ connects JVM with OS-dependent native libraries.

