Server	Needs external server setup	Embedded servers (Tomcat/Jetty) included
Setup	Time-consuming	Quick setup with starters
Opinionated	No	Yes, provides defaults
Real-time example:РђеYou want to create a REST API quickly. With Spring Boot, you can run a standalone app with embedded Tomcat using @SpringBootApplication, without setting up XML configs or external servers.

2. Explain Spring Boot auto-configuration. How does it work internally?
Answer:РђеAuto-configuration automatically configures Spring beans based on the dependencies present in the classpath.
* Internally, Spring Boot uses @EnableAutoConfiguration to load configurations from spring-boot-autoconfigure module.
* It checks conditions using @ConditionalOnClass, @ConditionalOnMissingBean, etc.
Real-time example:РђеIf spring-boot-starter-data-jpa is on the classpath, Spring Boot automatically configures EntityManagerFactory, DataSource, and TransactionManager without manual setup.

3. What are starters in Spring Boot and why are they used?
